</span>
3 Months</div></div><div
class="how-to-desc"><div
class="how-to-image">
<picture>
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-how-to-start-a-nail-salon-800x800-2020101.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=250&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="250" height="250" alt="How to Start a Nail Salon:">
</picture></div><p>The nail salon market is a highly lucrative one that is fairly easy to enter and has historically been resilient to most economic downturns. Overall, it's an attractive industry to enter, but there's a lot of competition. As such, you will need a solid business strategy and ways to differentiate your nail salon from others.</p></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section1" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>1.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=decide-what-type-of-nail-salon-you-would-like-to-open>Decide what type of nail salon you would like to open.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section1-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=choose-what-type-of-nail-salon-you-039-d-like-to-start>Choose what type of nail salon you&#039;d like to start.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-choose-what-type-of-nail-salon-you-would-like-to-start-288x288-2020107.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Choose what type of nail salon you&#039;d like to start."></div></div><p>You will need to decide which of the various types of nail salons to open, i.e., a home-based, solo operation; a retail nail salon in a busy suburb; or a mobile nail salon.</p><p><strong>Ask yourself the following questions:</strong></p><ul><li><p>What type of services will you provide?</p></li><li><p>Will you offer basic manicures and pedicures, or will you provide full-service treatments, i.e., color application, acrylics, nail art, and massages?</p></li><li><p>Will you offer fancy decor and a relaxing ambiance with soothing music playing in the background, or a speedy in-and-out service with nail technicians set up at stations around the room?</p></li><li><p>How will your business stand out from other nail salons?</p></li><li><p>Do you have a cosmetology license?</p></li></ul></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section1-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=define-your-target-market>Define your target market.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-define-your-target-market-288x288-20200817_2020-08-17-082654.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Define your target market."></div></div><p>If you want to provide the best nail services in your area, you will need to understand who your customer is.</p><p><strong>Survey potential customers.</strong> Create a questionnaire and ask people in your neighborhood to fill it out to give you an idea of what treatments they like and are willing to pay for.</p><p><strong>Figure out who your customer is.</strong> Will you target stay-at-home moms, busy professionals, or both? By knowing who your customer is, you will have a better idea of which services to offer, how to style your space, and how to advertise your services.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section1-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=determine-your-niche>Determine your niche.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-determine-your-niche-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Determine your niche."></div></div><p>Once you've completed your research and understand your customers' needs and expectations, you can think about your niche, i.e., what sets your business apart from others, and how your nail salon fits into the competitive landscape.</p><p><strong>Which nail services are you skilled at?</strong> Perhaps you are skilled at acrylic nails, in which case your main service could focus on providing acrylic manicures and pedicures. If you'd prefer to offer all services, make sure you have the necessary qualifications and training to provide them.</p><p><strong>Find your niche.</strong> Instead of serving all types of customers, you could focus on serving bridal parties, corporate functions, birthdays, or private functions. Alternatively, you could put together all-inclusive packages.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section2" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>2.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=create-a-business-plan>Create a business plan.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section2-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=write-an-executive-summary>Write an executive summary.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-write-an-executive-summary-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Write an executive summary."></div></div><p>An executive summary should include your mission statement, your product or service, and a brief description of your company's leadership team, employees, location, and growth plan.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Download the business plan template toward the top of this page to get started.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section2-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=write-a-company-description>Write a company description.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-write-a-company-description-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Write a company description."></div></div><p>Your company description should provide detailed information about your business's purpose, such as what problems your business plans to solve and how it stands out from your competitors.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section2-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=include-your-market-research>Include your market research.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-do-a-swot-analysis-288x288-20200817_2023-09-26-033953_kxrc.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Include your market research."></div></div><p>Your market research and SWOT analysis ensure that you understand the demographics of your customers, as well as your competitors' strengths and weaknesses. Therefore, your marketing strategy should describe how you plan to attract and retain clients.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section2-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=describe-your-organization-and-management>Describe your organization and management.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-describe-your-organization-and-management-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Describe your organization and management."></div></div><p>This section should elaborate on how your business will be legally structured and who will run it.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section2-step5" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.5&nbsp;</span><h4 id=describe-your-finances>Describe your finances.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-describe-your-finances-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Describe your finances."></div></div><p>If you plan on applying for funding, your business plan should include your financial outlook for the next three to five years. Use this section to convince the reader that your business idea is viable.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section3" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>3.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=form-your-business>Form your business.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section3-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=choose-a-business-name>Choose a business name.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-choose-a-business-name-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Choose a business name."></div></div><p>If you haven't yet thought of a name for your nail salon, now is the time to do so. Think of a few names that you think would best describe the services you are planning to offer.</p><ul><li><strong>If you are a sole proprietor:</strong> Sole proprietors can use their name as the business name and will not have to register with the state. However, if you choose an alternate name for your business, you'll need to register under a "doing business as" (DBA) name.</li><li><strong>Entity name:</strong> Depending on your business structure and location, you may be required to register your business name as a legal entity name. This will prevent another company from operating under the same name.</li><li><strong>Trademark:</strong> If you plan to open a chain of nail salons, you will be required to <a
href="https://www.namesnack.com/guides/how-to-do-a-trademark-search">apply for a trademark</a>. We recommend doing so even if it isn't mandatory, since a trademark will deter other businesses from using your name as their own.</li><li><strong>DBA name:</strong> Your location and business structure will dictate whether you need to register a DBA name. A DBA allows you to conduct business under a different identity from your own.</li></ul><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Use a <a
href="https://www.namesnack.com/">business name generator</a> if you need name ideas for your business.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section3-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=choose-a-legal-structure>Choose a legal structure.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-familiarize-yourself-with-the-key-business-structures-288x288-20200820_2023-09-26-034248_vpna.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Choose a legal structure."></div></div><p>Before you register your business as a legal entity with the state, you'll need to select a legal structure. There are several types of legal structures to choose from.</p><p>If you plan on starting a mobile nail salon or working from home, a sole proprietorship would be a suitable option. However, for a full-service nail salon with a location, you'll want to separate your personal assets from your business's assets and debts.</p><p>In this case, a Limited Liability Company (LLC) or Limited Liability Partnership (LLP) might be a suitable option from a tax and liability standpoint. Your decision will also depend on whether you want to issue stock to raise capital.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>If you are unsure about which legal structure to choose, consult an attorney to help you make the right choice for your business.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section3-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=register-your-business-as-a-legal-entity>Register your business as a legal entity.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-register-your-business-in-indiana-288x288-20200917_2023-09-26-034328_kydm.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Register your business as a legal entity."></div></div><p>Once you have chosen a legal structure, go ahead and register your business with the Secretary of State or your local business filing agency, and pay the required fees.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section3-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=hire-a-registered-agent>Hire a registered agent.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-hire-a-registered-agent-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Hire a registered agent."></div></div><p>If you register as a partnership or LLC, you may need to hire a registered agent. A registered agent is an individual who is designated to receive "service of process" (SOP) correspondence, such as tax forms and notice of lawsuits, from the state.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>While you can serve as your own registered agent, it is advisable to hire a third party to be responsible for receiving important documents if, for any reason, you are not available. Registered agent services cost between $100 and $300 per year.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section3-step5" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.5&nbsp;</span><h4 id=obtain-a-federal-tax-id-number-and-state-tax-id>Obtain a federal tax ID number (EIN) and state tax ID.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-irs-ein-application-288x288-20200624_2023-09-26-034512_vzij.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Obtain a federal tax ID number (EIN) and state tax ID."></div></div><p>In order to open a business bank account, hire employees, and apply for a business license and permits, you'll need to get an Employee Identification Number (EIN). Fortunately, it's free to apply for one. All you have to do is go to the <a
href="https://www.irs.gov/businesses/small-businesses-self-employed/apply-for-an-employer-identification-number-ein-online">IRS website</a>, complete your application online, and you'll receive your EIN immediately.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Note that there are seven states that do not charge state income tax; these are <a
href="https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-business-in-alaska">Alaska</a>, <a
href="https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-business-in-florida">Florida</a>, <a
href="https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-business-in-nevada">Nevada</a>, <a
href="https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-business-in-south-dakota">South Dakota</a>, <a
href="https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-business-in-texas">Texas</a>, <a
href="https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-business-in-washington">Washington</a>, and <a
href="https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-business-in-wyoming">Wyoming</a>.</p></div><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>To find out how to apply for an EIN, take a look at our <a
href="https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-apply-for-an-ein">guide</a>.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section3-step6" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.6&nbsp;</span><h4 id=find-out-if-you-need-to-withhold-state-income-tax>Find out if you need to withhold state income tax.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-find-out-if-you-need-to-withhold-state-income-tax-288x288-2020101.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Find out if you need to withhold state income tax."></div></div><p>In addition to federal tax, most states charge income tax, which requires employers to withhold earnings from their employees' wages or salaries. That said, if you are a sole proprietor, you are required to report all income and losses on your personal income tax return — this is called "pass-through" taxation.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section3-step7" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.7&nbsp;</span><h4 id=apply-for-a-licenses-and-permits>Apply for a licenses and permits.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-obtain-applicable-licenses-and-permits-288x288-20200812-1_2023-09-26-034635_qlam.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Apply for a licenses and permits."></div></div><p>Now that you have registered your business and acquired an EIN, it's time to get your business license and permits.</p><p><strong>Obtain a state/city/county license.</strong> Because you are opening a nail salon, you will not have to apply for a federal license. However, you will need to obtain a state, city, or county license depending on your location and business activities. Each state, city, and county has its own regulations, so visit your state's website to find out which licenses and permits you require.</p><p><strong>Obtain a seller's permit.</strong> In many states, you will have to get a seller's permit in order to sell products in your nail salon. This is so that your state/city/county can charge sales tax on the transactions you make. If, however, you live in <a
href="https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-business-in-alaska">Alaska</a>, <a
href="https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-business-in-delaware">Delaware</a>, <a
href="https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-business-in-montana">Montana</a>, <a
href="https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-business-in-new-hampshire">New Hampshire</a>, or <a
href="https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-business-in-oregon">Oregon</a>, you do not need a seller's permit as these states do not impose sales tax.</p><p><strong>Obtain a cosmetology license.</strong> Licensing requirements vary by location, but you will likely need to obtain an operating license from your local cosmetology board. In addition, your staff will need to have completed state-approved training before they can serve customers.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section3-step8" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.8&nbsp;</span><h4 id=open-a-business-bank-account>Open a business bank account.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-open-a-business-bank-account-288x288-20200728_2023-09-26-034713_ajez.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Open a business bank account."></div></div><p>Now that you have your federal EIN, you can proceed to open a business bank account.</p><p><strong>Choose a bank account that suits your needs.</strong> There are several types of accounts that you can open, ranging from savings accounts to merchant accounts, which allow you to accept both debit and credit card payments from your customers. To open a business bank account, you will need:</p><ul><li>Your EIN (or Social Security Number if you're a sole proprietor).</li><li>Business license.</li><li>Business formation documents.</li></ul></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section3-step9" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.9&nbsp;</span><h4 id=purchase-business-insurance>Purchase business insurance.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-obtain-business-insurance-288x288-20200728_2023-09-26-034752_ugkn.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Purchase business insurance."></div></div><p>It's advisable to obtain business insurance to protect your nail salon from unexpected risks, such as a lawsuit or property damage. You'll also need to provide workers' compensation insurance for your staff. Consult an insurance agent to learn more.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section4" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>4.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=secure-funding>Secure funding.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section4-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=determine-how-much-capital-you-will-need>Determine how much capital you will need.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-determine-how-much-capital-you-will-need-288x288-2020101.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Determine how much capital you will need."></div></div><p>To get your business off the ground, you will need to obtain start-up capital in order to rent a space, obtain licenses and permits, and purchase inventory, etc.</p><p>You'll want to work out your costs and make projections. Be as realistic as possible and model a best-case scenario as well as a worst-case scenario.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>If financials are not your strong suit, we suggest consulting an accountant.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section4-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=fund-your-business-with-personal-savings>Fund your business with personal savings.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-fund-your-business-with-personal-savings-288x288-2020101.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Fund your business with personal savings."></div></div><p>One of the most common ways to raise start-up capital is through bootstrapping. Most financial experts recommend investing your own personal savings into your business as you won't have to repay anyone later.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section4-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=ask-family-and-friends-for-a-loan>Ask family and friends for a loan.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-ask-family-and-friends-for-a-loan-288x288-20201007.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Ask family and friends for a loan."></div></div><p>Your friends and family may offer more favorable loan terms than banks and alternative lenders.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section4-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=get-a-business-credit-card>Get a business credit card.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-get-a-business-credit-card-288x288-2020101.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Get a business credit card."></div></div><p>Many start-ups use personal and/or business credit cards to obtain funding for small purchases, such as equipment and supplies, to start generating cash flow.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section4-step5" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.5&nbsp;</span><h4 id=apply-for-a-small-business-loan>Apply for a small business loan.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-apply-for-a-small-business-loan-288x288-2020101.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Apply for a small business loan."></div></div><p>To get a small business loan for your nail salon you will need to have a business plan, a decent credit score, and projections for the next few years to assure the lender that you can repay them. Be sure to compare offers to get the best rates and terms.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section4-step6" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.6&nbsp;</span><h4 id=try-crowdfunding>Try crowdfunding.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-try-crowdfunding-288x288-20200814_2023-09-26-042411_vmrj.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Try crowdfunding."></div></div><p>The advantage of crowdfunding is that there is low risk due to the fact that crowdfunders typically do not ask for shares in your business and do not expect anything in return.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section4-step7" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.7&nbsp;</span><h4 id=apply-for-an-sba-loan>Apply for an SBA loan.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-apply-for-an-sba-loan-288x288-20200820_2023-09-26-042456_aclh.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Apply for an SBA loan."></div></div><p>The Small Business Administration (SBA) provides low-interest loans to businesses that do not qualify for traditional financing. There are six different SBA options to choose from, guaranteeing loans up to $5 million.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>SBA lenders will be able to talk through each of these with you to help establish the best option for your business.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section5" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>5.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=determine-your-pricing-strategy>Determine your pricing strategy.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section5-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>5.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=do-a-sales-forecast>Do a sales forecast.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-do-a-sales-forecast-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Do a sales forecast."></div></div><p>Your pricing strategy depends on your financial projections, target market, competitors, and available funds. With the competitive landscape and target audience considered, it's important to find a price point that will attract customers and allow you to turn a profit.</p><p>Doing a sales forecast, and projected profit and loss statement, will assist you in defining the right price point that creates a profit and is still attractive to customers.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section5-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>5.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=price-your-services>Price your services.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-price-your-services-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Price your services."></div></div><p>Look at your offerings and at your client base to determine how price-sensitive they are. To accomplish this, you will need to perform an in-depth comparison of all your competitors, looking at their value offering to determine what the appropriate price point would be. You should also consider the time and effort that goes into providing your services, as well as your supply costs.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>At first, you may need to charge lower prices while you build up your brand. Focus on elements such as quality products, exceptional service, and marketing to boost your reputation and create a strong brand identity. Once your brand is recognizable and your customers trust you, you can think about increasing your prices.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section6" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>6.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=set-up-your-nail-salon>Set up your nail salon.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section6-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=pick-a-location>Pick a location.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-pick-a-location-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Pick a location."></div></div><p>Your location will depend on what is convenient for your target market, local zoning laws, available spaces, and pricing.</p><p><strong>Choose a location based on your target market.</strong> Considering the demographics of your target market will help you determine where the best location for your nail salon should be. For example, if you're targeting busy female professionals, you could provide a mobile service by traveling to clients' homes or places of work. Alternatively,  you could lease a space inside a business park.</p><p><strong>Research potential zoning restrictions.</strong> Regardless of whether you're opening a home-based or retail nail salon, be sure to check what commercial activities your city or county allows in your neighborhood to avoid violating any zoning regulations.</p><p><strong>Consider the cost of opening a retail location.</strong> A retail nail salon will cost between $40,000 and $125,000 to build from the ground up. The most economical option is to rent retail space, such as a former hair salon or restaurant, that already comes equipped with power and water.</p><p><strong>Be mindful of standard nail salon sizes and dimensions.</strong> The size of an average nail salon is 1,000–1,500 square feet. The area size of a manicure station is roughly 16 square feet, with the space required for a pedicure being double the size at 32 square feet. Your retail and reception area will fit into roughly 100 square feet. This means you'll be able to fit 10–12 nail technicians into an average size nail salon. Budget for between $75 and $125 per square foot.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section6-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=refurbish-or-furnish-your-nail-salon>Refurbish or furnish your nail salon.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-refurbish-or-furnish-your-nail-salon-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Refurbish or furnish your nail salon."></div></div><p>If you hire a retail space, you can refurbish and turn it into the nail salon that you envision. Bear in mind that rental prices vary and will depend on your location.</p><p>Good locations include shopping malls or areas with high foot traffic, such as those close to restaurants and shops. Keep in mind that these areas will probably charge higher rentals, so you will need to balance the cost of attracting clients with the amount of space you can afford.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section6-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=obtain-a-certificate-of-occupancy>Obtain a certificate of occupancy.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-obtain-a-certificate-of-occupancy-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Obtain a certificate of occupancy."></div></div><p>When renting a retail space, you will need to obtain a certificate of occupancy (CO) from your local government, which is a legal document that shows that you comply with all building regulations and that your space is safe to be occupied.</p><p>If you're renting a space, it's likely that a CO already exists on file, in which case you can purchase a copy. The cost of a CO varies from state to state, but you can expect to pay between $100 and $1,000 depending on your county or city.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section6-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=purchase-software-to-run-your-business-smoothly>Purchase software to run your business smoothly.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-purchase-salon-management-software-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Purchase software to run your business smoothly."></div></div><p>In retail, merchants use a point of sale (POS) system to process sales and accept cash and credit card payments. There are many POS systems available, with both free and paid options.</p><p>A POS system will help you to keep track of your sales and allow you to manage your expenditure and inventory effectively. If you integrate the POS system with your accounting system, data will automatically be saved, making your salon more efficient.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>If you are running a nail salon with several employees, you'll want to obtain salon management software to manage all your appointments, as well as inventory management software to keep track of your stock. Salon management software ranges from free to $129.00 per month, while inventory management software ranges from free to $199.00 per month.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section6-step5" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.5&nbsp;</span><h4 id=purchase-supplies-and-decorate-your-space>Purchase supplies and decorate your space.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-purchase-supplies-and-decorate-your-space-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Purchase supplies and decorate your space."></div></div><p>Some of the items that you will need to run your business day-to-day include manicure stations, chairs, and other furniture. However, new equipment can be costly, so consider purchasing second-hand equipment to minimize your start-up costs.</p><p>After you've stocked your inventory, decorate your space to make it look attractive for clients.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Look for a wholesale supplier in your area from whom you can purchase all of your supplies in bulk.</p></div><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Be sure to refer back to your business plan in which you should have an itemized inventory of all the supplies you will need.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section6-step6" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.6&nbsp;</span><h4 id=get-signage-and-branded-materials>Get signage and branded materials.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-get-signage-and-branded-materials-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Get signage and branded materials."></div></div><p>Attract people passing by your salon with outdoor signage, and provide branded materials like price lists and brochures.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section7" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>7.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=start-hiring>Start hiring.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section7-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=hire-employees>Hire employees.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-hire-employees-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Hire employees."></div></div><p>Hiring reliable and hardworking people takes time and effort. Therefore, it's important to follow a structured process that will help you to find and hire the best employees for your nail salon.</p><p><strong>Decide how you will pay your staff.</strong> Will you only pay employees a base salary, or will they also earn a commission?</p><p>Follow these steps when you're ready to start hiring:</p><ul><li>Write a job posting.</li><li>Post on a job board.</li><li>Review applications and resumes.</li><li>Interview candidates.</li><li>Check references.</li><li>Send a job offer letter.</li><li>Fill out the mandatory IRS forms.</li><li>Train employees.</li></ul><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>There are many hiring tools and job posting software that you can leverage to help you find and hire the best nail technicians. You may also want to use an applicant tracking system to help streamline the process.</p></div><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Visit the <a
href="https://www.bls.gov/ooh/personal-care-and-service/manicurists-and-pedicurists.htm">Bureau of Labor Statistics website</a> for information about the median wage estimates for manicurists and pedicurists.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Once you've hired employees, get them to fill out and return Form W-4 for tax purposes.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section7-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=set-up-payroll-for-your-staff>Set up payroll for your staff.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-set-up-payroll-for-your-staff-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Set up payroll for your staff."></div></div><p>Next, you'll want to set up payroll and schedule pay periods to withhold taxes for the IRS. If you prefer to outsource this task, you can hire a payroll company to do it for you.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Consider offering your employees the added benefit of a good retirement plan. There are many small business retirement plan options to choose from that will help you, as the owner, save as well.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section8" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>8.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=open-your-salon>Open your salon.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section8-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>8.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=have-a-grand-opening-to-attract-customers>Have a grand opening to attract customers.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-have-a-grand-opening-288x288-20200817_2023-09-26-043535_qvii.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Have a grand opening to attract customers."></div></div><p>A great way to attract customers to your nail salon is by hosting a grand opening. Create a digital invitation and invite your friends, family, and nearby businesses to a low-key event at your store before the opening date.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nail-salon-section8-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>8.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=ensure-that-cleanliness-standards-are-followed>Ensure that cleanliness standards are followed.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-ensure-that-cleanliness-standards-are-followed-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Ensure that cleanliness standards are followed."></div></div><p>Careful steps should be taken to keep nail salon instruments clean, as it is easy for bacteria, fungi, and even viruses to be transferred between customers and employees.</p><p>The U.S. Environmental Protection Agency has published a guide for nail salon owners titled "<a
href="https://nepis.epa.gov/Exe/ZyPDF.cgi/60000F3A.PDF?Dockey=60000F3A.PDF">Protecting the Health of Nail Salon Workers</a>," which provides best practices related to sanitizing instruments and ensuring safety and cleanliness in the salon.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
